<HEAD>Poll Indicates Voters Believe Kohl Should Be Replaced</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A poll indicates Chancellor Helmut
Kohl's popularity is at an all-time low and that most West German
voters want a change of leadership, a newspaper reported Sunday.
   Welt am Sonntag newspaper published the results of a recent poll
conducted by the Wickert Institute, which reported that 64.2
percent of the voters polled wanted Kohl replaced; 35.8 percent
wanted him to stay on as chancellor.
