140 companies and foundations nationwide. The institute polled
2,410 registered voters in 324 localities over a seven-day period.
The poll's margin of error was not given.
   Kohl's conservative Christian Democratic Union party has lost
ground in state elections since Kohl was re-elected in 1987. Most
recently the party lost control of the Frankfurt city government.
   The loss of popularity stems in part from a scandal over the
involvement of West German companies in an alleged Libyan chemical
weapons plant.
