<HEAD>Dollar Firms Slightly, Stock Prices Edge Down In Early Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. dollar firmed slightly in early trading
against the Japanese yen Monday, while stock prices edged down.
   The dollar opened at 131.68 yen, up 0.41 yen from Friday's close
of 131.27 yen.
   A dealer with the Bank of Tokyo said there was some demand for
the dollar but otherwise the market was extremely quiet in the wake
of a three-day Easter holiday overseas.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, a 20.14-point loser Friday, shed another 14.97
points, or 0.04 percent, shortly after the market opened to move to
31,553.55.
   Currency and stock markets in New York will reopen Monday, while
both markets in London will be closed until Tuesday.
